documentary.%20She%20spoke%20to%20a%20handful%20of%20reporters%20in%20her%20office%20%E2%80%94%20which%20was%20covered%20in%20personal%20photos%20and%20colorful%20furniture%20%E2%80%94%20alongside%20Obaid-Chinoy%2C%20Dalton%2C%20and%20producers%20Fabiola%20Beracasa%20Beckman%20and%20Tracy%20Aftergood.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20designer%20has%20no%20shortage%20of%20success%20in%20her%20career%2C%20but%20during%20the%20press%20conference%2C%20she%20said%20her%20wrap%20dress%20is%20still%20her%20greatest%20source%20of%20professional%20pride.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22266d806c-53e4-4beb-a79c-1b0176009ac5%5C%22%3EThe%20wrap%20dress%20changed%20von%20Furstenberg's%20life%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EVon%20Furstenberg%20created%20the%20wrap%20dress%20in%201973%2C%20taking%20inspiration%20from%20ballerina's%20tops%20and%20bright%20fabrics%20she%20first%20saw%20in%20Italy%2C%20as%20she%20shared%20in%20the%20documentary.%20She%20originally%20sold%20wrap%20tops%20with%20skirts%20but%20turned%20the%20silhouette%20into%20one%20garment%20after%20seeing%20Julie%20Nixon%20Eisenhower%20wearing%20them%20together.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20dress%20became%20a%20staple%20in%20millions%20of%20women's%20wardrobes%2C%20with%20von%20Furstenberg%20making%2015%2C000%20wrap%20dresses%20each%20week%20by%201975%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.cnn.com%2F2008%2FWORLD%2Famericas%2F11%2F17%2Fdiane.von.furstenberg%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ECNN%20reported%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Celebrities%20have%20also%20been%20spotted%20wearing%20wrap%20dresses%20over%20the%20years%2C%20from%20Oprah%20Winfrey%20to%20Karlie%20Kloss%2C%20both%20of%20whom%20are%20featured%20in%20the%20documentary.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThat%20dress%20became%20a%20phenomenon%2C%26quot%3B%20von%20Furstenberg%20said%20in%20%26quot%3BWoman%20in%20Charge.%26quot%3B%20%26quot%3BIt%20became%20the%20first%20dress%20for%20so%20many%20people%20for%20the%20first%20job%2C%20for%20the%20first%20interview.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%