%20offer%20and%20were%20set%20to%20close%20in%20June.%20Right%20around%20this%20time%2C%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Fwhat-is-the-federal-reserve%5C%22%3EFederal%20Reserve%3C%2Fa%3E%20raised%20interest%20rates.%20This%20led%20to%20our%20buyer%20backing%20out%20the%20same%20week%20of%20closing.%20They%20said%20they%20could%20no%20longer%20afford%20the%20mortgage.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20market%20began%20to%20shift%20rapidly%20from%20a%20seller's%20to%20a%20buyer's%20market%20in%20our%20area.%20While%20this%20was%20a%20major%20blow%2C%20my%20husband%20and%20I%20had%20to%20reframe%20our%20strategy%2C%20and%20we%20were%20thankful%20to%20finally%20sell%20our%20home%20in%20December%20%E2%80%94%20nearly%20six%20months%20after%20originally%20listing%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20learned%20that%20selling%20a%20house%20at%20any%20time%20is%20possible%2C%20but%20you%20need%20to%20be%20flexible%20and%20change%20your%20strategy%20to%20adapt%20to%20what's%20going%20on%20in%20your%20community.%20Here%20are%20four%20strategies%20that%20helped%20us%20sell%20during%20a%20rocky%20time.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E1.%20We%20strategically%20switched%20Realtors%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EI%20can't%20stress%20enough%20how%20important%20choosing%20the%20right%20Realtor%20for%20the%20job%20is.%20When%20buying%20and%20selling%20our%20first%20home%2C%20my%20husband%20and%20I%20were%20a%20little%20lax%20when%20it%20came%20to%20selecting%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Fhow-to-find-real-estate-agent%5C%22%3Ereal-estate%20agent%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20didn't%20really%20ask%20the%20right%20questions.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20made%20the%20tough%20but%20necessary%20decision%20to%20start%20fresh%20with%20a%20new%20Realtor.%20I%20specifically%20chose%20someone%20who%20had%20several%20excellent%20references%2C%20was%20working%20in%20our%20area%2C%20and%20was%20closing%20many%20deals%20on%20the%20buyer%20side.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20wanted%20someone%20who%20worked%20with%20many%20buyers%20to%20get%20a%20better%20insight%20into%20what%20buyers%20were%20looking%20for%20now.%20I%20figured%20this%20Realtor%20could%20show%20our%20home%20to%20some%20of%20her%20clients%20to%20speed%20up%20the%20showing%20process.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20strategy%20paid%20off.%20Our%20Realtor%20suggested%20repairs%20and%20upgrades%20to%20make%20the%20house%20more%20move-in-ready%20and%20appealing%20to%20buyers.%20These%20were%20things%20I%20probably%20wouldn't%20have%20thought%20of%20on%20my%20own.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAdditionally%2C%20our%20Realtor%20had%20connections%20with%20affordable%20contractors%2C%20landscapers%2C%20cleaners%2C%20and%20more%20to%20help%20streamline%20the%20process%20of%20getting%20the%20work%20done.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E2.%20We%20figured%20out%20the%20right%20price%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EOur%20Realtor%20was%20very%20realistic%20about%20what%20buyers%20expect%20and%20compared%20the%20features%20of%20our%20homes%20to%20those%20of%20others%20that%20were%20being%20sold.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EJust%20a%20year%20prior%2C%20homes%20in%20our%20area%20had%20been%20sold%20at%20crazy%20high%20prices%20and%20receiving%20bids%20well%20over%20asking.%20We%20paid%20attention%20to%20feedback%20from%20showings%20as%20well%20as%20what%20was%20going%20on%20in%20the%20community%20to%20come%20up%20with%20a%20competitive%20and%20realistic%20price.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%20the%20listing%20went%20up%20and%20we%20didn't%20receive%20any%20offers%2C%20we%20adjusted%20the%20price%20once%20and%20received%20an%20offer%20shortly%20after.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E3.%20We%20considered%20different%20loan%20types%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EAt%20first%2C%20I%20was%20afraid%20to%20accept%20offers%20from%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Ffha-loan%5C%22%3EFHA%20loan%3C%2Fa%3E%20buyers.%20Our%20home%20was%20older%2C%20and%20I%20had%20heard%20that%20FHA%20had%20stricter%20requirements.%20I%20didn't%20know%20if%20our%20home%20was%20truly%20up%20to%20FHA%20standards%20since%20we%20bought%20it%20with%20a%20conventional%20loan.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20we%20were%20missing%20out%20on%20many%20quality%20buyers.%20I%20realized%20a%20lot%20of%20people%20were%20choosing%20FHA%20since%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Faverage-mortgage-interest-rate%5C%22%3Emortgage%20rates%3C%2Fa%3E%20were%20slightly%20better%20at%20the%20time.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20ended%20up%20selling%20the%20home%20to%20a%20borrower%20with%20FHA%20funding%2C%20and%20the%20process%20was%20not%20that%20bad%20at%20all.%20We%20made%20some%20minor%20repairs%20and%20fixes%2C%20but%20I'm%20glad%20we%20opened%20ourselves%20up%20to%20accept%20several%20different%20types%20of%20loans.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E4.%20We%20were%20open%20to%20negotiation%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EAnother%20thing%20I%20feel%20that%20helped%20us%20sell%20our%20home%20in%20a%20changing%20market%20was%20our%20willingness%20to%20negotiate%20and%20decide%20in%20advance%20what%20we'd%20be%20willing%20to%20offer.%20The%20buyers%20wanted%20a%20credit%20for%20%242%2C500%2C%20and%20while%20I%20didn't%20agree%20with%20it%2C%20we%20decided%20to%20honor%20their%20request%20to%20keep%20the%20deal%20going.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAt%20that%20time%2C%20we%20were%20paying%20the%20mortgage%20for%20our%20empty%20home%20as%20well%20as%20rent%20at%20our%20new%20home.%20We%20were%20also%20responsible%20for%20keeping%20the%20utilities%20on%20at%20our%20empty%20home%20and%20paying%20for%20landscaping.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESo%20offering%20this%20credit%20to%20seal%20the%20deal%20made%20sense%20financially%20to%20relieve%20us%20of%20those%20extra%20payments.%20We%20also%20agreed%20to%20include%20a%20home%20warranty%20for%20the%20buyers%20for%20%24900.%20This%20was%20a%20drop%20in%20the%20bucket%20compared%20to%20what%20we'd%20be%20paying%20if%20the%20deal%20fell%20through%20and%20the%20house%20remained%20on%20the%20market.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThis%20article%20was%20originally%20published%20in%20August%202023.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbuyer-backed-out-change-our-house-selling-strategy-2024-6%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1717625522000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F643064b73007470019fe2ab2%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbuyer-backed-out-change-our-house-selling-strategy-2024-6%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22We%20were%20fully%20ready%20to%20sell%20our%20house%20last%20June%20when%20the%20Federal%20Reserve%20raised%20interest%20rates.%20We%20had%20to%20rethink%20our%20strategies%20for%20selling.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22insider%40insider.com%20(Chonc%C3%A9%20Maddox)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbuyer-backed-out-change-our-house-selling-strategy-2024-6%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Ex-OpenAI%20employee%20speaks%20out%20about%20why%20he%20was%20fired%3A%20'I%20ruffled%20some%20feathers'%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%227732%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22OpenAI%20logo%20dark%20background%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6660919fcc442a2f676e2c23%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%225155%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EFormer%20OpenAI%20former%20employee%20Leopold%20Aschenbrenner%20spoke%20out%20about%20his%20firing.%3Cp%3EJaap%20Arriens%2FGetty%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3ELeopold%20Aschenbrenner%20spoke%20about%20his%20firing%20from%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhistory-of-openai-company-chatgpt-elon-musk-founded-2022-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EOpenAI's%3C%2Fa%3E%20superalignment%20team%20in%20a%20podcast.%C2%A0%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EHe%20said%20HR%20warned%20him%20after%20he%20shared%20a%20memo%20about%20OpenAI's%20security%20with%20two%20board%20members.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EHe%20said%20his%20firing%20was%20related%20to%20sharing%20a%20brainstorming%20doc%20with%20outside%20researchers.%C2%A0%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EA%20former%20OpenAI%20researcher%20opened%20up%20about%20how%20he%20%26quot%3Bruffled%20some%20feathers%26quot%3B%20by%20writing%20and%20sharing%20some%20documents%20related%20to%20safety%20at%20the%20company%2C%20and%20was%20eventually%20fired.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELeopold%20Aschenbrenner%2C%20who%20graduated%20from%20Columbia%20University%20at%2019%2C%20according%20to%20his%20LinkedIn%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fopenai-ends-superalignment-team-manage-ai-risks-2024-5%23%3A~%3Atext%3DOpenAI%2520created%2520its%2520Superalignment%2520team%2Ctheir%2520resignations%2520earlier%2520this%2520week.%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eworked%20on%20OpenAI's%20superalignment%20team%3C%2Fa%3E%20before%20he%20was%20reportedly%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Faffiliate.insider.com%3Fh%3Ddc3c9e2ea524d0776413c606b4a4b8a6b6c6f4dd9d9a9af43f9cb0edbb6de368%26postID%3D66606ec4e01a10ede1bed577%26postSlug%3Dformer-openai-researcher-leopold-aschenbrenner-interview-firing-2024-6%26site%3Dbi%26u%3Dhttps%253A%252F%252Fwww.theinformation.com%252Farticles%252Fopenai-researchers-including-ally-of-sutskever-fired-for-alleged-leaking%5C%22%20data-autoaffiliated%3D%5C%22true%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%26quot%3Bfired%20for%20leaking%26quot%3B%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20April.%20He%20spoke%20out%20about%20the%20experience%20in%20a%20recent%20interview%20with%20podcaster%20Dwarkesh%20Patel%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.dwarkeshpatel.com%2Fp%2Fleopold-aschenbrenner%23footnote-1-145136502%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ereleased%3C%2Fa%3E%20Tuesday.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAschenbrenner%20said%20he%20wrote%20and%20shared%20a%20memo%20after%20a%20%26quot%3Bmajor%20security%20incident%26quot%3B%20that%20he%20didn't%20specify%20in