y're%20not%20actually%20against%20contraception%20but%20have%20other%20issues%20with%20the%20bill.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EThe%20vote%20was%20widely%20seen%20as%20a%C2%A0%26quot%3Bshow%20vote%26quot%3B%20that%20had%20little%20chance%20of%20becoming%20law%20anyway.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Senate%20failed%20on%20Wednesday%20to%20advance%20a%20bill%20designed%20to%20protect%20access%20to%20contraceptives%20nationwide.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EJust%20two%20Republican%20senators%20%E2%80%94%20Susan%20Collins%20of%20Maine%20and%20Lisa%20Murkowski%20of%20Alaska%20%E2%80%94%20voted%20with%20Democrats%20to%20advance%20the%20bill.%20Nine%20Republicans%20did%20not%20show%20up%20to%20vote.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20vote%20was%20teed%20up%20by%20Senate%20Majority%20Leader%20Chuck%20Schumer%20as%20part%20of%20an%20effort%20to%20highlight%20the%20different%20between%20the%20Democratic%20and%20Republican%20parties%20over%20reproductive%20rights%20ahead%20of%20an%20election%20where%20abortion%20is%20expected%20to%20play%20a%20major%20role.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERepublicans%20derided%20the%20effort%20as%20a%20%26quot%3Bshow%20vote%2C%26quot%3B%20arguing%20that%20no%20one%20is%20seriously%20interested%20in%20banning%20contraceptives%20such%20as%20condoms%2C%20Plan-B%2C%20or%20IUDs.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BDo%20people%20really%20think%20that%20even%20a%20significant%20minority%20of%20the%20Republican%20conference%20is%20against%20access%20to%20contraception%3F%26quot%3B%20said%20Republican%20Sen.%20Thom%20Tillis%20of%20North%20Carolina.%20%26quot%3BI%20don't%20even%20want%20to%20get%20into%20what%20I%20don't%20like%20about%20the%20bill.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20true%20that%20the%20effort%20is%20largely%20for%20show%20%E2%80%94%20Schumer%20and%20Democrats%20knew%20that%20the%20GOP-controlled%20House%20would%20not%20take%20up%20the%20legislation.%20To%20that%20point%2C%20the%20bill's%20%26quot%3Bfindings%26quot%3B%20section%20argues%20that%20access%20for%20contraception%20is%20%26quot%3Bespecially%20critical%20for%20historically%20marginalized%20groups%26quot%3B%20including%20%26quot%3BBlack%2C%20indigenous%2C%20and%20other%20people%20of%20color%2C%26quot%3B%20%26quot%3Bimmigrants%2C%26quot%3B%20and%20%26quot%3BLGBTQ%2B%20people.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20not%20necessarily%20untrue%2C%20it's%20not%20the%20sort%20of%20thing%20one%20would%20put%20in%20legislation%20designed%20to%20attract%20the%20support%20of%20conservative%20Republicans.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt's%20a%20bill%20that%20has%20a%20lot%20of%20other%20garbage%20in%20it%2C%20and%20this%20is%20a%20messaging%20exercise%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Tillis.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20still%20%E2%80%94%20if%20Republicans%20aren't%20against%20contraception%2C%20why%20won't%20they%20just%20vote%20for%20the%20bill%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20you%20ask%20them%2C%20it%20mainly%20comes%20down%20to%20religious%20freedom.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%225c6c40d0-3e14-4064-ba1e-d24a3b261bc3%5C%22%3E'The%20number%20one%20issue%20with%20it'%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.congress.gov%2Fbill%2F118th-congress%2Fsenate-bill%2F1999%2Ftext%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EDemocratic%20bill%3C%2Fa%3E%20is%20designed%20to%20guarantee%20the%20right%20to%20access%20contraception%2C%20which%20was%20first%20established%20for%20married%20couples%20by%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20in%20its%201965%20%3Cem%3EGriswold%20v.%20Connecticut%3C%2Fem%3E%20ruling.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESome%20experts%20have%20since%20worried%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcontraception-access-privacy-rights-at-risk-overturned-roe-v-wade-2022-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ethat%20right%20could%20now%20be%20at%20risk%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20the%20wake%20of%20the%20overturning%20of%20Roe%20v.%20Wade%20in%202022.%20In%20his%20concurring%20opinion%20in%20that%20case%2C%20Justice%20Clarence%20Thomas%20argued%20that%20Griswold%20should%20be%20revisited.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20the%20bill%20includes%20a%20line%20stating%20that%20it%20%26quot%3Bapplies%20notwithstanding%20any%20other%20provision%20of%20Federal%20law%2C%20including%20the%20Religious%20Freedom%20Restoration%20Act%20of%201993.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20law%20essentially%20protects%20individuals'%20right%20to%20religious%20freedoms.%20Republicans%20argue%20waiving%20that%20law%20amounts%20to%20a%20%26quot%3Bpoison%20pill%26quot%3B%20in%20the%20bill%20that%20would%20force%20religious%20institutions%20to%20provide%20contraceptives.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThey've%20said%20basically%2C%20contraception%20is%20gonna%20be%20allowed%20everywhere%2C%20regardless%20of%20your%20faith%2C%20your%20background%2C%20your%20institution%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Republican%20Sen.%20James%20Lankford%20of%20Oklahoma.%20%26quot%3BThat's%20the%20number%20one%20issue%20with%20it.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELike%20other%20Republicans%2C%20Lankford%20is%20also%20opposed%20to%20certain%20forms%20of%20medical%20care%20for%20transgender%20youth.%20The%20bill%20includes%20%26quot%3Bsterilization%26quot%3B%20under%20its%20definition%20of%20contraception%2C%20which%20the%20Oklahoma%20Republican%20argued%20would%20interfere%20with%20state-level%20bans%20on%20gender-affirmed%20care%20for%20people%20under%2018.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThis%20would%20remove%20that%20right%20from%20all%20those%20states%20to%20say%20they're%20protecting%20minors%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Lankford.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E22%20GOP%20senators%2C%20led%20by%20Sen.%20Rick%20Scott%20of%20Florida%2C%20signed%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.rickscott.senate.gov%2F2024%2F6%2Fsen-rick-scott-leads-colleagues-in-slamming-democrats-attacks-on-religious-freedoms-parental-rights-political-games-on-contraception%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Estatement%3C%2Fa%3E%20on%20Tuesday%2C%20declaring%20that%20there's%20%26quot%3Bno%20threat%20to%20access%20to%20contraception%26quot%3B%20and%20that%20the%20bill%20%26quot%3Binfringes%20on%20the%20parental%20rights%20and%20religious%20liberties%20of%20some%20Americans.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDemocrats%20have%20also%20attempted%20to%20pass%20similar%20legislation%20at%20the%20state%20level%2C%20but%20have%20been%20blocked%20by%20Republicans.%20Last%20month%2C%20Republican%20Gov.%20Glenn%20Youngkin%20of%20Virginia%20vetoed%20a%20bill%20to%20protect%20access%20to%20contraception%2C%20arguing%20that%20it%20violated%20principles%20of%20religious%20freedom.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22eb3f5201-592e-4b4b-8a9c-30b88ebefe04%5C%22%3EThe%20Republicans%20who%20voted%20to%20block%20the%20bill%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EHere%20are%20the%2038%20GOP%20senators%20who%20voted%20to%20block%20the%20Right%20to%20Contraception%20Act%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EJohn%20Barrasso%20of%20Wyoming%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EMarsha%20Blackburn%20of%20Tennessee%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EJohn%20Boozman%20of%20Arkansas%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3ETed%20Budd%20of%20North%20Carolina%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EShelley%20Moore%20Capito%20of%20West%20Virginia%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EBill%20Cassidy%20of%20Louisiana%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EJohn%20Cornyn%20of%20Texas%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3ETom%20Cotton%20of%20Arkansas%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EKevin%20Cramer%20of%20North%20Dakota%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EMike%20Crapo%20of%20Idaho%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3ETed%20Cruz%20of%20Texas%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3ESteve%20Daines%20of%20Montana%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EJoni%20Ernst%20of%20Iowa%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EDeb%20Fischer%20of%20Nebraska%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EChuck%20Grassley%20of%20Iowa%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EJosh%20Hawley%20of%20Missouri%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EJohn%20Hoeven%20of%20North%20Dakota%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3ECindy%20Hyde-Smith%20of%20Mississippi%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3ERon%20Johnson%20of%20Wisconsin%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EJames%20Lankford%20of%20Oklahoma%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EMike%20Lee%20of%20Utah%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3ECynthia%20Lummis%20of%20Wyoming%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3ERoger%20Marshall%20of%20Kansas%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EMitch%20McConnell%20of%20Kentucky%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EMarkwayne%20Mullin%20of%20Oklahoma%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3ERand%20Paul%20of%