ors%20shared%20personal%20stories%20of%20addiction%2C%20revealing%20the%20scale%20of%20the%20issue.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A118%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bbc.com%2Fnews%2Farticles%2Fc722vr3wprlo%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Starlink%20Brings%20Internet%20To%20Remote%20Tribe.%20They%20Get%20Hooked%20To%20Porn%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20dense%20Amazon%20rainforest%2C%20lives%20an%20indigenous%2C%20remote%20tribe%20that%20speaks%20its%20language%2C%20and%20has%20a%20different%20culture%20preserved%20for%20several%20millennia.%20However%2C%20a%20technological%20marvel%20has%20breached%20its%20isolated%20existence%20-%20Elon%20Musk's%20revolutionary%20Starlink%20satellite%20internet%20service.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EYet%2C%20with%20this%20newfound%20connection%20comes%20a%20dilemma%2C%20echoing%20through%20the%20elders'%20concerns%20and%20the%20tribe's%20evolving%20dynamics.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nytimes.com%2F2024%2F06%2F02%2Fworld%2Famericas%2Fstarlink-internet-elon-musk-brazil-amazon.html%5C%22%3EThe%20New%20York%20Times%3C%2Fa%3E%20met%20the%20Marubos%2C%20the%202000-member%20tribe%20which%20connected%20with%20the%20world%20through%20the%20internet%20for%20the%20first%20time.%20Billionaire%20Elon%20Musk's%20Starlink%20provides%20internet%20to%20remote%20locations%20or%20areas%20that%20have%20had%20normal%20communications%20infrastructure%20disabled%20through%20low-Earth%20orbit%20satellites.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EInternet%20services%20penetrated%20the%20jungles%20of%20the%20Amazon%20in%20September%20last%20year%20when%20the%20services%20were%20launched%20in%20Brazil.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWhen%20it%20arrived%2C%20everyone%20was%20happy%2C%26quot%3B%2073-year-old%20Tsainama%20Marubo%20told%20the%20New%20York.%20The%20internet%20brought%20clear%20benefits%2C%20like%20video%20chats%20with%20faraway%20loved%20ones%20and%20calls%20for%20help%20in%20emergencies.%20%26quot%3BBut%20now%2C%20things%20have%20gotten%20worse%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BYoung%20people%20have%20gotten%20lazy%20because%20of%20the%20internet%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%20%26quot%3BThey're%20learning%20the%20ways%20of%20the%20white%20people.%26quot%3B%20And%20added%2C%20%26quot%3BBut%20please%20don't%20take%20our%20internet%20away.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20tribe%20now%20faces%20a%20fundamental%20dilemma%20-%20The%20uses%20of%20the%20internet%20and%20its%20impact%20on%20their%20culture.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20youth%20are%20now%20hooked%20to%20their%20phones%20-%20They%20are%20chatting%20with%20friends%2C%20glued%20to%20screens%2C%20and%20accessing%20pornography%20and%20misinformation.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESpeaking%20to%20the%20NYT%2C%20Alfredo%20Marubo%2C%20leader%20of%20a%20Marubo%20association%20of%20villages%2C%20has%20emerged%20as%20the%20tribe's%20most%20vocal%20critic%20of%20the%20internet.%20He%20said%20He%20is%20most%20unsettled%20by%20the%20pornography.%20He%20said%20young%20men%20were%20sharing%20explicit%20videos%20in%20group%20chats%2C%20a%20stunning%20development%20for%20a%20culture%20that%20frowns%20on%20kissing%20in%20public.%20%26quot%3BWe're%20worried%20young%20people%20are%20going%20to%20want%20to%20try%20it%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said%20of%20the%20graphic%20sex%20depicted%20in%20the%20videos.%20He%20said%20some%20leaders%20had%20told%20him%20they%20had%20already%20observed%20more%20aggressive%20sexual%20behaviour%20from%20young%20men.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhile%20some%20parents%20are%20happy%20their%20children%20will%20not%20get%20an%20education%2C%20their%20concerns%20surrounding%20the%20cons%20of%20the%20internet%20remain.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20antennas%20were%20donated%20to%20the%20tribe%20by%20American%20Entrepreneur%2C%20Allyson%20Reneau.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20advent%20of%20the%20internet%20is%20seen%20as%20a%20positive%20too%20for%20the%20remote%20tr