208%3A22%20pm%20(IST)%20from%20the%20Space%20Launch%20Complex-41%20at%20Cape%20Canaveral%20Space%20Force%20Station%20in%20Florida.%20This%20is%20her%20third%20space%20flight.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20lift-off%20happened%20on%20the%20third%20attempt%20and%20was%20nominal.%20The%20Starliner%20got%20the%20correct%20orbit%20and%20will%20dock%20with%20the%20International%20Space%20Station%20a%20day%20later.%20Today%2C%20the%20US%20has%20three%20crewed%20spacecraft%20simultaneously%20in%20orbit%20-%20the%20Boeing%20Starliner%2C%20the%20SpaceX%20Crew%20Dragon%2C%20and%20the%20International%20Space%20Station.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENASA%20says%20if%20all%20goes%20well%20the%20Starliner%20will%20dock%20to%20the%20forward-facing%20port%20of%20the%20station's%20Harmony%20module%20and%20Ms%20Williams%20and%20her%20co-passenger%20Butch%20Wilmore%20will%20remain%20at%20the%20space%20station%20for%20about%20a%20week%20to%20test%20the%20spacecraft%20and%20its%20subsystems%20before%20NASA%20works%20to%20complete%20the%20final%20certification%20of%20the%20transportation%20system%20for%20rotational%20missions%20to%20the%20orbiting%20laboratory%20as%20part%20of%20its%20Commercial%20Crew%20Program.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Starliner%20has%20been%20designed%20for%20astronauts%20by%20astronauts%20and%20is%20the%20most%20modern%20crew%20module%20ever%20to%20be%20flown%2C%20NASA%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMs%20Williams%2C%20a%20poster%20girl%20for%20women%20aspiring%20to%20fly%20into%20space%2C%20flew%20into%20the%20skies%20in%20a%20brand-new%20spacecraft.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EEarlier%2C%20the%20Indian-origin%20astronaut%20had%20spent%20322%20days%20in%20space%20and%20held%20a%20record%20for%20the%20maximum%20hours%20of%20spacewalk%20by%20a%20woman%2C%20before%20being%20overtaken%20by%20Peggy%20Whitson.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20time%2C%20she%20makes%20history%20as%20the%20first%20woman%20to%20fly%20on%20a%20maiden%20crewed%20mission%20of%20a%20new%20space%20shuttle.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%2059-year-old%20admitted%20to%20being%20a%20bit%20nervous%20but%20said%20she%20had%20no%20jitters%20about%20flying%20in%20a%20new%20spacecraft%20that%20she%20helped%20design%20with%20engineers%20from%20NASA%20and%20Boeing.%20%26quot%3BWhen%20I%20reach%20the%20International%20Space%20Station%2C%20it%20will%20be%20like%20going%20back%20home%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20nearly%2010-day%20mission%20will%20help%20the%20Starliner%20prove%20its%20space-worthiness.%20It%20would%20also%20prove%20the%20team's%20readiness%20to%20get%20a%20NASA%20certification%20and%20fly%20long-duration%20missions%20for%20the%20US%20space%20agency.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Starliner%20is%20much%20behind%20schedule%20and%20way%20over%20the%20budget%2C%20with%20some%20saying%20that%20the%20problems%20plaguing%20Boeing%20in%20its%20aviation%20business%20may%20be%20spilling%20into%20its%20space%20business.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%202014%20NASA%20awarded%20a%20%244.2%20billion%20contract%20for%20its%20making%20from%20scratch%20and%20ten%20years%20later%20it%20has%20not%20seen%20even%20a%20single%20successful%20human%20space%20flight.%20In%20contrast%2C%20Space%20X%20which%20was%20given%20a%20similar%20contract%20for%20the%20development%20of%20Crew%20Dragon%20was%20delivered%20at%20an%20estimated%20cost%20of%20%242.6%20billion.%20SpaceX%20is%20already%20ferrying%20astronauts%20to%20the%20ISS%20using%20its%20crew%20module.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1717602120000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2024-06%2Fq1bksob8_boeing-starliner-lifts-off-ndtv_625x300_05_June_24.jpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findians-abroad%2Findian-origin-astronaut-sunita-williams-scripts-history-as-she-rockets-into-space-onboard-boeing-starliner-5825911%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Indian-origin%20astronaut%20Sunita%20Williams%20rocketed%20into%20space%20creating%20history%20as%20the%20first%20woman%20to%20test%20a%20spacecraft%20on%20its%20maiden%20mission%2C